A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for Cab Booking System (like Ola / Uber).

Requirements:

Riders can request a ride by providing pickup and drop location.
System should find nearby available drivers.
Rider can see estimated fare and driver details.
Driver can accept or reject the ride request.
Once accepted, track the ride in real-time (basic status).
Handle ride completion and payment (mocked).
Prevent multiple drivers being assigned to the same ride.

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is acceptable.
Focus on core matching and booking flow.
Support basic concurrency (multiple ride requests).

Edge Cases:

No driver available nearby.
Driver rejects the request.
Rider cancels the ride.
Same driver accepting multiple rides.

B. HAPPY PATH STORY

=> Rahul is in Whitefield, Bangalore and wants to go to Koramangala.
=> He opens the app, enters pickup and drop location, and requests a ride.
