C. 6 MANDATORY STEPS FOR LLD DESIGN

1. Clarify requirements

=> Functional: Request ride, find nearby drivers, driver accept/reject, track ride status, complete ride.
=> Non-Functional: Fast driver matching, handle concurrent ride requests.
=> Assumptions: Single city, simple distance-based fare, location is mocked as string.
=> Edge Cases: No drivers, driver rejection, rider cancellation, double booking.

2. Identify entities and relationships

=> Main Entities: Rider, Driver, Ride, Location, Vehicle
=> Key relationships :
Ride belongs to one Rider and one Driver.
Driver has one Vehicle.
Ride has status and locations (pickup, drop).

